textEntry.text: WORK FORCE CHANGES:  According to published reports, Apple announced the opening of its location in Malaysia at the heart of the new Tun Razak Exchange (TRX) business centre in Kuala Lumpur.

eventType.description: Media Report of Intent to Change Work Force

textEntry.text: ANNOUNCED WORK FORCE CHANGES:  According to published reports, Apple announced that it is planning to cut jobs from iPhone assembly lines by up to 50 percent through increased automation in the coming years, as the company might be looking to improve efficiency and address supply chain vulnerabilities.

eventType.description: Media Report of Work Force Change

textEntry.text: WORK FORCE CHANGES:  According to published reports, Apple announced that the company unveiled its newest flagship store in Indonesia, located in the city of Jakarta.
MERGER/ACQUISITION:  According to published reports, Apple, DUNS 060704780, (Cupertino, CA) announced the acquisition of WaveOne.

eventType.description: Media Report of Intent to Change Work Force

textEntry.text: ANNOUNCED WORK FORCE CHANGES:  According to published reports, Apple announced that it has inked a lease agreement to build a new Apple Store at Miami Worldcenter, set to show up by 2025 at the earliest. The one-story structure will be located at the corner of Northeast Eighth Street, to the west of the Jewel Box retail building at 725 NE First Avenue, Miami, FL.

ANNOUNCED WORK FORCE CHANGES:  According to published reports, Apple announced that it will soon open a new retail store at Square One Shopping Centre, considered the largest mall in Ontario and the second largest in Canada. There are still no details about when the new store will open, but the current one will be permanently closed once that happens.
